      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "> Wouldn't this add additional network load for nodes, albeit small, considering it is one transaction every 6 hours?\r\n\r\nOn average it would be once every 3 hours, since it chooses a random point in time within a 6 hour range.\r\nHowever, since we make feeler connections every 2 minutes, I don't think the bandwidth increase is worth considering. The extra overhead of a private broadcast connection vs a feeler is just an inv -> getdata -> tx and ping + pong.\r\n",
